article.headline: Creighton 68, Iona 62
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Nate Funk scored 18 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Creighton made 12 3-pointers in a 68-62 victory over Iona in Tuesday's final of the Omaha Regional in the Guardians Classic. Johnny Mathies and Kellen Miliner added 14 points each and Jimmy Motz added 12 for Creighton (2-0). Ricky Soliver led Iona (1-1) with 21 points. Greg Jenkins added 16 points and Steve Burtt had 13. The Gaels lost despite shooting 47 percent (21-of-45) to Creighton's 37 percent (19-of-52). But the Bluejays had six more 3-pointers and enjoyed a 36-25 edge in rebounds. Iona led 46-42 with 12 minutes to play when a 9-0 run on three 3-pointers put the Bluejays ahead for good. Soliver's 3-pointer made it 51-49 before an 9-2 burst, including a 3-pointer by Funk, made it 59-51 with 5:42 to play. That was enough for Creighton, but not before Iona clawed within five with 1:53 left. Two free throws by Funk with 1:27 made it 64-57 and Iona responded 10 seconds later with a 3-point play by Burtt. Funk and Miliner sandwiched two free throws each around a layup by Burtt in the final 25 seconds. Iona led 32-31 following a spirited first half that featured 12 3-pointers, seven by the Bluejays, and 12 lead changes. Soliver scored 13 points in the first half and Mathies, a reserve, had 12 on 4-of-5 shooting, including 3-of-3 on 3-pointers as the Creighton bench outscored Iona's 14-2. The Bluejays advance to play Missouri the Guardians Classic semifinals Nov. 23 at 8:00. They'll be joined by Ohio State, which plays Houston in the other semifinal.
